messageBody:
Is there an assertNotEquals()...

Having just written the following test ( to confirm/disprove a possible
bug with a hash code generation code) I saw that there is

assertSame()
assertNotSame()

assertTrue()
assertFalse()

assertEquals()

but no
assertNotEquals()

which means I have to do: assertFalse((obj1.equals(obj2)));

I know its not a big deal, I just feel assertEquals is missing its expected
pair.

Andy



public void testEqualsMethodAgainstNonEquilantObjects() {
/*INFO: AlarmPaneModel: adding lifecycle:
Current NoteID= 19,
LifeCycleID= 5,
Severity= Indeterminate,

Cause= UNSUPPORTED_CAUSE,

MOC= site,
Source= telosRHbsc,
EventTime= Fri Mar 14 15:03:10 GMT 2003,
AddText= 35220:Site::OML:Comms:Crit:Manuf:OML link fail
*/
AlarmLifeCycleKey key1 = new
AlarmLifeCycleKey(AlarmEventFactory.createMockAlarmEvent("BSS=0,SITE=452",
AlarmType.COMMUNICATIONS, ProbableCause.UNSUPPORTED_CAUSE));

/*INFO: AlarmPaneModel: updating lifecycle:
Current NoteID= 72,
LifeCycleID= 5,
Severity= Warning,
Acked= false,

MOI= BSS=0,SITE=1025, MOC= site,
Source= telosRHbsc,
EventTime= Thu Mar 20 15:15:01 GMT 2003,
AddText= 41535:WARN:Site:OML:dhcp_fsm.c#1563:DHCP TFTP download failed
during startup
*/
AlarmLifeCycleKey key2 = new
AlarmLifeCycleKey(AlarmEventFactory.createMockAlarmEvent("BSS=0,SITE=1025,
MOC= site", AlarmType.PROCESSING_ERROR, ProbableCause.IPA_BTS_SW_WARNING));

assertFalse((key1.equals(key2)));
}
